reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Reliable Performance and Great Value
reviews.reviewText: I recently upgraded my PC with the MSI B450M PRO, and I couldn't be happier with the results. This motherboard offers a great combination of features, performance, and value for AMD, making it an excellent choice for both casual users and gamers.Compatibility and Performance:The B450M PRO-VDH Max even though was specifically designed for AMD Ryzen 2nd and 3rd Gen processors can be used with 4th and 5th gen after a Bios update, and it offers excellent compatibility. I paired it with a Ryzen 3 3200g CPU while I am able to get a graphics card, and it has consistently delivered exceptional performance. Whether I'm working on graphic-intensive tasks or (for now) light gaming, this motherboard handles it all with ease. Remember to use fast DDR4 ram since Ryzen CPUs really make good use of it.Micro-ATX Form Factor:The Micro-ATX form factor of this motherboard is perfect for those looking to build a compact PC without sacrificing performance. It fits into smaller cases, making it a great choice for compact and portable builds.M.2 Slot and USB 3:The M.2 slot for SSDs ensures speedy data transfers and quick system boot times. Additionally, the USB 3 ports offer fast data transfer speeds and are handy for connecting external storage devices or peripherals. This motherboard truly delivers when it comes to connectivity and speed.D-Sub, DVI, and HDMI Ports:The inclusion of D-Sub, DVI, and HDMI ports means you have multiple options for connecting displays if you use a "G" Ryzen CPU. Whether you're using a traditional monitor or a high-definition display, this motherboard has you covered. The graphics options are versatile and offer great flexibility.Reliability and Build Quality:MSI is known for its reliability and build quality, and the B450M PRO-VDH Max lives up to that reputation. It features solid construction and high-quality components, ensuring the longevity and stability of your system.Price and Value:One of the standout features of this motherboard is its affordability. It provides impressive performance and features for its price point, making it an exceptional value for budget-conscious builders.In conclusion, the MSI B450M PRO-VDH Max Micro-ATX Motherboard is a top-notch choice for anyone seeking a reliable, budget-friendly motherboard for AMD Ryzen processors. It delivers impressive performance, boasts a range of connectivity options, and its Micro-ATX form factor makes it suitable for compact builds. Whether you're a casual user or a gamer, this motherboard has you covered without breaking the bank. I highly recommend it for anyone looking to upgrade or build a new AMD-based system. It's a five-star performer in terms of value and functionality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good enough when on sale, chipset limits RAM capacity (!!!)
reviews.reviewText: I recommend this motherboard only when it's on sale (=<$70) and only when the bare essentials are needed AND you don't mind not having the most up-to-date support for the latest generation of Ryzen CPU's as of late 2023. This also means PCIe 3.0 instead of latest PCIe 4.0, something which may be of great importance in certain PC builds e.g. using newer graphics cards which utilize a PCIe 4.0x4 connection and even PCIe 4.0x8 cards in some scenarios.VERY IMPORTANT NOTE: "Due to chipset resource usage, the available capacity of [RAM] memory will be a little less than the amount of installed." [sic] -- This is straight from the motherboard manual off the MSI website (not sure if this manual even came with the motherboard). What this means for my system is 13.9 GB of usable RAM (!!!) instead of the 16 GB (2x8 GB) I bought. I'm not certain if this is a limitation of the B450 chipset (in which case, my lack of due diligence is to blame) or of the admittedly cheap RAM I bought, but, regardless, something this important should be highlighted with a corresponding amount of emphasis on the product page. It should definitely not be relegated to a single bullet point in a manual you have to download yourself! Luckily, I have not really run into issues with the lowered RAM capacity in my day-to-day use, but it's definitely something to keep in mind. On the plus side, I was able to configure XMP for my RAM.I was able to install a Ryzen 5 4600G after some troubleshooting since the BIOS version installed out-of-the-box was from April of this year. If you are installing a Ryzen chip that is newer than the 3000 series, I highly recommend that you DO NOT factory reset the BIOS during your troubleshooting like I almost did; you may be effed if you don't have a spare compatible AMD CPU in this situation. My early troubleshooting issues were ones that come with building a new PC and not so much a fault of the motherboard itself. It has not really given me any hardware/software/firmware issues, which speaks to its stability.Overall, this is a good, reliable, and cheap motherboard, but one that will likely kneecap your RAM capacity!

reviews.reviewText: Superbe carte mère niveau rapport qualité prix, elle est géniale !De plus, la mise à jour BIOS a été effectué et donc, j'ai pu mettre un Ryzen 5 5600G sans problème.

Amazing performance for price. All important ports and features, enough USB3 ports. Good Bios. Already updated for Ryzen 3000 series. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 10, 2019

reviews.reviewText: I had lots of ram problems with my previous budget motherboard, Gigabyte B450m DS3H Motherboard when i bought 3200MHz ram. Went so far as to even buy a new ram kit because i thought my ram was faulty. EVentually i realised it was the motherboard that wasn't able to keep up with the ram OC. I ended up purchasing this motherboard and it worked like a charm! So easy to OC with minimal requirement on my end to tweak any voltages or timings, just a simple XMP setting and i was good to go. It's great.However, I realise price of this motherboard fluctuates quite abit. Just be on the look out for a deal. I bought this motherboard for SGD154 including shipping.
